[h1]Break[/h1]

The [b]break [/b]statement "jumps out" of a loop and continues executing the code after the loop.[code format="js" codeId="673"]for (i = 0; i <= 10; i++) {
   if (i == 5) {
     [b]break[/b]; 
   }
   document.write(i + "<br />");
}[/code]
Once i reaches 5, it will break out of the loop. [img id="2758" width="100%"]

quizzes.question:
What is the output of this code?
var sum=0; 
for(i=4; i<8; i++) {
  if (i == 6) {
    continue; 
  }
  sum += i;
}
document.write(sum);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Continue[/h1]

The [b]continue [/b]statement breaks only one iteration in the loop, and continues with the next iteration.[code format="js" codeId="674"]for (i = 0; i <= 10; i++) {
   if (i == 5) {
      [b]continue; [/b]
   }
   document.write(i + "<br />");
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b] [img id="2759" width="100%"]
[note]The value 5 is not printed, because [b]continue [/b]skips that iteration of the loop.[/note]
